 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.2","title":"CI E2E Matrix and Artifact Upload Gate","description":"Run required e2e matrix lanes in CI (correctness/recovery/concurrency tiers) and upload structured logs plus repro bundles as artifacts on failure.","design":"Use scenario matrix metadata as single source for lane generation to avoid manual workflow drift.","acceptance_criteria":"- Required E2E matrix lanes (correctness/recovery/concurrency/compat) run in CI with deterministic seeds.
- Failure artifact upload includes logs, seed manifest, scenario IDs, and replay instructions.
- Matrix includes explicit pass/fail policy for required vs optional lanes.","notes":"E2E gate track now combines matrix execution/artifact durability (bd-mblr.3.2.1) with scenario-to-script drift detection (bd-mblr.3.2.2), ensuring required scenarios remain both mapped and executed with reproducible evidence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:58.297984521Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.580691529Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.844209325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:42:38.530941313Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1349,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CI artifact policy: on failure, upload logs + reduced repro + mismatch diagnostics + environment manifest. Artifacts must be sufficient for offline replay by another engineer/agent.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:13Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","title":"CI E2E matrix workflow + artifact publishing","description":"Implement CI matrix for scenario workloads with deterministic seeds and durable artifact upload policy. Output: reproducible matrix runs with retained diagnostics.","design":"Implement matrix definition as data (manifest) plus renderer, not hand-authored duplicated YAML blocks.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI matrix generation is deterministic and traceable to canonical scenario/seed manifests.
- Artifact publishing is robust: every failure lane produces complete triage bundle with retention policy.
- Workflow output surfaces run_id/scenario_id links so investigators can jump directly to relevant evidence.","notes":"Treat artifact durability as first-class; missing artifacts on failure should itself fail the job. Detailed log-quality conformance is enforced in downstream gates (bd-mblr.3.2.2 and bd-mblr.5.5.3), allowing core matrix/artifact workflow implementation to proceed earlier.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:51:19.230787773Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.966556362Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.464845668Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","title":"Scenario-to-script coverage drift CI gate","description":"Add CI checker that validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test traceability manifests and fails when required scenarios are unmapped or unexecuted in required lanes. Output: machine-readable gap diff and human summary.","design":"Compare canonical scenario catalog against script/test traceability and executed lane manifests to detect both mapping drift and execution drift.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test manifests and required execution lanes. 2. Fails when required scenarios are unmapped or not executed with required artifacts/logging. 3. Produces machine-readable gap diff and concise operator summary for remediation.","notes":"This gate consumes consolidated script-suite readiness via bd-mblr.4.5.3 and core matrix behavior via bd-mblr.3.2.1; redundant parent blocker edges are removed where sequencing is already guaranteed transitively.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.043386147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:52:28.538262260Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.633253091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:46.539768818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.363805786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.905989905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.3.3","title":"Flake Budget, Retry Policy, and Quarantine Workflow","description":"Define explicit flake budget for unit/e2e/coverage jobs, safe retry strategy, quarantine process, and escalation path so CI gates stay reliable without masking real regressions. Output: policy + automation hooks + incident workflow.","design":"Model flake handling as policy config + enforcement hooks so decisions are reviewable and versioned.","acceptance_criteria":"- Flake budget is numerically defined per gate class with clear escalation thresholds.
